### **Practical Task (Sales_Data Table)**

| OrderID | Product  | Quantity | Price | OrderDate |
| ------- | -------- | -------- | ----- | --------- |
| 1001    | Laptop   | 2        | 1200  | 1/5/2023  |
| 1002    | Mouse    | 5        | 25    | 2/5/2023  |
| 1003    | Keyboard | 1        | 80    | 2/5/2023  |
| 1004    | Monitor  | 1        | 300   | 3/5/2023  |
| 1005    | Laptop   | 1        | 1200  | 3/5/2023  |

#### Add a Calculated Column: **TotalSales = Quantity Ã— Price**

```DAX
TotalSales = Sales_Data[Quantity] * Sales_Data[Price]
```

Resulting Table:

| OrderID | Product  | Quantity | Price | OrderDate | TotalSales |
| ------- | -------- | -------- | ----- | --------- | ---------- |
| 1001    | Laptop   | 2        | 1200  | 1/5/2023  | 2400       |
| 1002    | Mouse    | 5        | 25    | 2/5/2023  | 125        |
| 1003    | Keyboard | 1        | 80    | 2/5/2023  | 80         |
| 1004    | Monitor  | 1        | 300   | 3/5/2023  | 300        |
| 1005    | Laptop   | 1        | 1200  | 3/5/2023  | 1200       |

#### Measure: **Total Revenue**

```DAX
TotalRevenue = SUM(Sales_Data[TotalSales])
```

ðŸ‘‰ **Total Revenue = 2400 + 125 + 80 + 300 + 1200 = 4105**
